Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.83,0:00:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today started out well.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.17,0:00:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But after the meeting tonight, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.05,0:00:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,my feelings were hurt.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.52,0:00:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier in the week, we invited \Nsome friends over to watch a movie.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.73,0:00:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And apparently, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.81,0:00:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,this new young elder heard about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.11,0:00:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so he counseled me about it \Nafter the meeting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.82,0:00:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,saying that I should give \Nmy movie choices \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.24,0:00:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,some thought.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.66,0:00:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I just didn’t like \Nthe way he gave the counsel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.66,0:00:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s only 27. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.70,0:01:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s too young.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.59,0:01:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day, \Nwe had plans to go out in the ministry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.01,0:01:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,with Brother Kang and his wife.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.93,0:01:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But the motivation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.35,0:01:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,just wasn’t there.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.36,0:01:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked to speak \Nwith Brother Kang alone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.36,0:01:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I told him what happened \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.36,0:01:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and how we didn’t feel \Nthe counsel applied to us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.20,0:01:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I can understand \Nhow you might feel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.70,0:01:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Byong Soo, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.12,0:01:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,be absolutely honest with me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.50,0:01:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you feel there is no valid reason \Nfor that counsel?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.30,0:01:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.35,0:01:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe there were some scenes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.68,0:02:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that could have been less violent. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.98,0:02:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But the way he gave the counsel\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.14,0:02:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,—he didn’t even ask how we felt.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.36,0:02:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Byong Soo, what is the only way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.27,0:02:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,for us to receive perfect counsel?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.49,0:02:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,From a perfect man.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.78,0:02:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.66,0:02:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And is Jesus here on the earth today?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.91,0:02:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He was right. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.25,0:02:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Counsel can only be perfect \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.79,0:02:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if it’s given from a perfect person.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.46,0:02:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, this counsel \Nabout our movie choices \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.34,0:02:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,would have been so much easier \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.59,0:02:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,if it came from someone older \Nand more experienced, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.51,0:02:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,like Brother Kang.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.52,0:02:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he must have sensed \Nwhat I was thinking \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.98,0:02:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because he helped me to remember \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.23,0:02:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,something from the Bible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.69,0:02:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When Job underwent severe trials, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.36,0:02:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it was the younger Elihu who helped Job \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.53,0:03:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,adjust his thinking correctly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.79,0:03:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It required humility on Job’s part \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.91,0:03:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to listen to someone younger \Nand less experienced.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.00,0:03:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He then read Proverbs 19:20: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.92,0:03:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“Listen to counsel and accept discipline, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.18,0:03:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to become wise in your future.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.60,0:03:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The point was clear: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.60,0:03:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep our focus on the counsel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.65,0:03:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not the counselor.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.33,0:03:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I later shared \NBrother Kang’s comments with my wife. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.33,0:03:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We both realized that we should welcome \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.00,0:03:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,all counsel from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.71,0:03:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s for our good.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.20,0:04:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure it took courage \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.70,0:04:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for that young elder \Nto approach me about the matter. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.12,0:04:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’m so glad he did because, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.46,0:04:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in the end, his counsel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.62,0:04:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,was just another example \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.42,0:04:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of God’s love.\N
